scene_description: the background is composed of black pixels. there are blue pixels and pink pixels spread out in the top half of the grid. at the bottom of the grid, there are two circles composed of lines made by grey pixels.
literal_instruction: remove all of the pink and blue pixels. to do this, replace each pink pixel or blue pixel with a blue pixel. then in the left circle on the base of the grid, fill the two bottom rows of the circle with blue pixels. in the right circle on the base of the grid, fill the first row with pink pixels. then, in the row above that, place a single pink pixel in the left-most space.
